          <h2>Causes & Risk Factors</h2>
          <p>The exact causes of bladder cancer are unknown; however, there are a number of factors which are responsible for this condition. There are a number of potential carcinogens which have been identified which are known to cause bladder cancer. The most important risk factors associated with this condition are:</p>
          <br>
              1. Smoking is one of the major risk factors which is responsible for causing bladder cancer.<br>
2. Exposure hazards at work: Certain chemicals are known to be carcinogenic and these can cause cancers. It is important to make sure that one is well protected from such exposure. <br>
3. Diet is also an important factor in determining cancer. It is believed that people who consume more fried meat and red meat are more prone to suffer from bladder cancer than those who donâ€™t.<br>
<br>
<p>The other factors that count are age, sex, race and even history of bladder cancer. Chronic bladder inflammation and birth defects may also cause bladder cancer.</p>
      </div>
